        Soil Chemistry and Analysis Syllabus
Instructor: Wan-Ru Chen Page 1
Soil Chemistry and Analysis (土壤化學與分析)
Level: Graduate
Instructor: 陳�膃p (Wan-Ru Chen), Ext 65841, e-mail: wruchen@mail.ncku.edu.tw
Class Time: Tuesday 1:00-3:00 pm, Thursday 3:00-4:00 pm Place: Rm. 47110
Office hour: Thursday 4:00-5:00 pm
Course Description：This course provides a background to soil chemistry and
instrumental methods of analysis with applications to soil characterization and
contamination compound measurement.
Course Schedule：
Week Date Topic
1 02/19, 02/21 Introduction
2 02/26 Soil basics I: The soil solid phase
3 03/05, 03/07 Soil basics II: Soil features and chemical characteristics
4 03/12, 03/14 Soil basics III: The biological and organic components in soil
5 03/19, 03/21 Soil basics IV: Exchange reactions in soil-sediment systems
6 03/26, 03/28 Soil basics V: Adsorption on soil colloids
7 04/02 Soil basics V: The Langmuir isotherm
8 04/09, 04/11 Midterm
9 04/16, 04/18 Soil basics VI: Oxidation-reduction reactions in soil systems
10 04/23, 04/25 Soil sampling: sampling, storage, and speciation
11 04/30, 05/01 Titrimetric measurements
12 05/07, 05/09 Extraction: Soxhlet extractor, ASE
13 05/14, 05/16 Soil characterization I: Electron microscope (SEM and TEM)
14 05/21, 05/23 Soil characterization I: BET, AFM
15 05/28, 05/30 Soil characterization II: Surface Analytical Techniques
Spectroscopy- XRD, XRF, IR
16 06/04, 06/06 Soil characterization II: Surface Analytical Techniques
Spectroscopy- XRD, XRF, IR
17 06/11, 06/13 Presentation
18 06/18, 06/20 Final Exam
